<TITLE> Another heavy defeat for hockey team </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 28 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh hockey team finished their four-nation Invitation International Hockey Tournament campaign with another heavy defeat -- 6-3 to hosts Russia in the place-deciding match in Moscow on Sunday. Bangladesh, who also lost to the Russians 4-2 in the group-phase match, were leading 2-1 at one stage before the first half ended in a 2-2 draw. They finally went down due to lack of experience, claimed team manger Anvir Adel. Jimmy, Manik and Rana struck one goal apiece for Bangladesh, who are scheduled to return home on Monday. They had earlier lost 6-2 to Canada and 8-0 to South Africa. bd
